A 17-year-old teenager, who allegedly stabbed a man to death with an iron rod, on Friday has been remanded by an Ebute Meta Magistrates’ Court in Lagos State. NAN reports that the Chief Magistrate, Mrs Adeola Adedayo, did not take the teenager’s plea on Friday but ordered that the defendant be kept at the Special Correctional Centre for Boys, Oregun, Lagos. The Prosecutor, Insp. Chinalu Uwadione, had told the court that the defendant committed the murder on Jan. 2 at 2.30a.m. at Tiwalade St., Sogunle, Oshodi. Uwadione said that the defendant used an iron rod to stab one 20-year-old Peter Udoh on the chest, causing his death. He noted that murder contravened Section 223 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. Adedayo adjourned the case until Feb. 5 for mention.